  "text": "Another example of a highly specialized amyloidogenic protein in plants is the elongation factor REF or Hevb1-a major component of latex in the \"rubber tree\" Hevea brasiliensis. REF participates in natural rubber biosynthesis, contains β-sheet organized aggregates with amyloid properties proven by circular dichroism (CD), TEM, infra-red spectroscopy and X-ray diffraction [CITATION_1] . Hevea is the genus of flowering plants in the spurge family used commercially for rubber production.",
